text: Thanks Melissa I'll have time in a few hours to check it out

Went through the prototype and it's looking good. I can see what you're saying about the final dashboard screens Melissa. Maybe it feels like there are a lot of transition screens and not a lot of change in between? But I do think they are helpful to set up the different states.
I'm not worried about it but think it's worth getting everyone's opinion.
<@U0GN0A9EV> <@U026103R3> <@U4VTSDW7P> ET got back to us on Care Asst naming - ADA is very high risk, but Ayda and AdaZ are the same risk; everyone at Care prefers Ayda, but Sheila likes AdaZ
so we ready to talk about it Monday
James and I prefer Ayda also, but lets get a handhold on that for Sheila
thanks <@U0260V1BX> I'm digging in to presentation and prototype now, will see if it feels like something's missing

The sequence of the final screens doesn't bother me after running through it a few times. 
The only thing that feels a little funny is that the rest is more detailed, but that might be fine since those are detailed flows vs dashboard states that will refresh based on context. 
I'll revisit in the morning with fresh eyes, and see if anything feels missing as I get further on the the big-picture overview
